The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Bengal emerged the overall champions in the East Zone Athletics that concluded on Tuesday. Bengal emerged champions in six events out of the total of eight bagging 110 medals including 50 golds. 

 The pensions of the 11 players were credited to CABs account by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI). According to a CAB official on Tuesday, they will distribute it to the cricketers shortly

 Brijesh Damani defeated David Bose 2-0 in the Baljit Securities West Bengal Open Snooker meet at the Bengal Rowing Club on Tuesday. 

 Army A routed Tamil Nadu Police 50-0 in the All India and South East Asian Rugby Championship at the CC amp;FC on Tuesday. In another match of the day, Future Hope got the better of Maharashtra State Police 21-12.




